  <h1 style="font-size:x-large; font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif">
Sruti Kendra is a non-profit spiritual service organisation founded by 
Svami Moksha Vidyaananda Sarasvati in 2011,head quartered in Chennai.Sruti Kendra’s 
objective is transform society and help people lead empowered lives through the value 
system and knowledge embedded in ancient Indian wisdom symbolised by our Vedas and 
Scriptures.This transformation in our Society will help us to lead peaceful, happy and
fulfilling lives in harmony with family, fellow beings and Nature. Another objective is
to develop pride in India’s great tradition and help Nation building. All activities of
Sruti Kendra are carried out in a socially inclusive manner.
<br/>
<br/>
Sruti Kendra has different wings –<br/> 
<a href='About.aspx#one'>Sruti Balakendra</a>, for children upto 12 years<br/>
<a href='About.aspx#two'> Sruti Yuvakendra</a>, for youth upto 20 years<br/>
<a href='About.aspx#three'>Sruti Sreekendra</a>, for developing and empowering women<br/>
<a href='About.aspx#four'>Sruti Shikshakendra</a>, for elders<br/>
<a href='About.aspx#five'>Sruti Sevakendra</a>, for service to less privileged in Society.<br/><br/>

The children’s wing (Balakendra) and youth wing (Yuvakendra) are two of the most 
important movements because children and youth are the change agents in society 
and developing the correct value system and developing their all round leadership
skills are very important for a great Society and Nation.
  <br/><br/>
  </h1>
